cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new reinforcement learning algorithm that addresses the issue of noisy environments and biased estimates in the early stages of learning. This makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the algorithm involves incorporating prior distributions and stochasticity, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on improving the learning rate and cost, which are key concerns in neural networks (cs.NE).
